T-Mobile US, Inc. {{IPAc-en|ˈ|t|iː|_|'|m|oʊ|b|ə|ˈ|l|_|juː|_|ɛ|s}} is an American [[Cellular network|wireless network operator]] headquartered in [[Overland Park, Kansas]], and [[Bellevue, Washington]], U.S.<ref name="10-K" /> Its largest shareholder is multinational telecommunications company [[Deutsche Telekom AG]], which {{as of|lc=yes|2023|April}}, holds a 51.4%<ref>{{Cite news |title=Deutsche Telekom to offload T-Mobile US shares. |work=Telecoms |url=https://telecoms.com/523459/deutsche-telekom-to-offload-t-mobile-us-shares/}}</ref> majority stake in the company.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Hardesty |first=Linda |date=2023-04-06 |title=Deutsche Telekom achieves majority stake in T-Mobile US |url=https://www.fiercewireless.com/wireless/deutsche-telekom-achieves-majority-stake-t-mobile-us |access-date=2023-04-09 |website=Fierce Telecom}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Keys |first=Matthew |date=2023-04-09 |title=Deutsche Telekom acquires majority of T-Mobile U.S. |url=https://thedesk.net/2023/04/deutsche-telekom-acquires-t-mobile-majority/ |access-date=2023-04-09 |website=The Desk |language=en-us}}</ref> T-Mobile US is the [[List of American mobile network operators|third-largest wireless carrier in the United States]], with 116.7 million subscribers at the end of Q2 2023.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Financial Results, Supplementary Data, Non-GAAP Reconciliations |url=https://s29.q4cdn.com/310188824/files/doc_financials/2023/q2/Q2-2023-ER-Tables-vFinal.xlsx |access-date=2023-10-05 |language=en-US}}</ref>

The company was founded in 1994 by [[John W. Stanton]] of the [[Western Wireless Corporation]] as VoiceStream Wireless. Deutsche Telekom then gained [[Plurality (voting)|plurality]] ownership in 2001 and renamed it after its [[T-Mobile International AG|T-Mobile]] brand. T-Mobile US provides wireless voice and data services in the United States under the T-Mobile and [[Metro by T-Mobile]] brands (the latter was acquired via the purchase of [[MetroPCS]] in a [[reverse takeover]] in 2013, resulting in T-Mobile going [[public company|public]] on the [[NASDAQ]] stock exchange), and also serves as the host network for many [[mobile virtual network operator]]s. The company has annual revenues of around $80 billion.<ref name="10-K"/> In 2015, [[Consumer Reports]] named T-Mobile the number one American wireless carrier.<ref name="money.cnn.com">{{cite web|title=Consumer Reports ranks T-Mobile as No. 1 carrier|url=https://money.cnn.com/2015/12/03/technology/t-mobile-verizon-consumer-reports/|publisher=CNNMoney.com|date=December 3, 2015}}</ref>

On April 1, 2020, T-Mobile and [[Sprint Corporation]] completed [[Merger of Sprint Corporation and T-Mobile US|their merger]], with T-Mobile now being the sole owner of Sprint, making Sprint an effective subsidiary of T-Mobile until the Sprint brand was officially discontinued on August 2, 2020, with the [[Sprint World Headquarters Campus|headquarters]] becoming T-Mobile offices.<ref name=":11"/><ref name=":12"/><ref name=":13"/> As part of the merger, T-Mobile US acquired [[Assurance Wireless]], the service subsidized by the [[Lifeline program|Lifeline Assistance program]] of the federal [[Universal Service Fund]].<ref name="USAToday2019"/>

{{main|Attempted purchase of T-Mobile USA by AT&T}}

On March 20, 2011, [[AT&T]] announced its intention to purchase T-Mobile US from Deutsche Telekom. The [[United States Department of Justice Antitrust Division|Antitrust Division]] of the [[United States Department of Justice]] responded by filing a federal lawsuit on August 31, 2011, to block the merger.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-31/u-s-files-antitrust-complaint-to-block-proposed-at-t-t-mobile-merger.html|title=U.S. Files to Block AT&T, T-Mobile Merger |date=August 31, 2011|accessdate=August 31, 2011|work=[[Bloomberg News|Bloomberg]]|first1=Tom|last1=Schoenberg|first2=Sara|last2=Forden|first3=Jeff|last3=Bliss
}}</ref> AT&T then decided to formally abandon the merger bid on December 19, 2011.<ref>{{cite web|author=AT&T |url=http://www.att.com/gen/press-room?pid=22146&cdvn=news&newsarticleid=33560&mapcode=corporate%7Cwireless-networks-general |title=AT&T Ends Bid To Add Network Capacity Through T-Mobile USA Purchase |publisher=AT&T |date=December 19, 2011 |accessdate=December 19, 2011}}</ref>

